	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64447420"><p>The "increasing public perception" is just that, a perception created by the media for eyeballs.  The reality is that violent crime is falling, has been falling for three decades, and there is no expectation that trend is likely to change any time soon.  On the other hand political violence is rising, again to large extent because of the media.  My recommendation to you would be to start to look a lot more critically at your media consumption, look for factual data rather than emotional statements (as few and far between as they may be).</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64447420">
